        "title": "Add LaunchDarkly feature flag support",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a LaunchDarkly React SDK provider with local fallback defaults when no client-side ID is configured.\n- Registers the `souls` app flag mapped to LaunchDarkly key `clawhub-souls`.\n- Gates Souls links on the header, footer, and home discovery category while keeping the `/souls` route reachable.\n- Adds LaunchDarkly setup docs plus `VITE_LAUNCHDARKLY_CLIENT_SIDE_ID` env docs.\n- Uses generated anonymous LaunchDarkly contexts so logged-out percentage rollouts bucket correctly.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bunx vitest run src/lib/features.test.ts src/lib/featureFlagContext.test.tsx src/__tests__/home-route.test.tsx src/__tests__/header.test.tsx src/components/Footer.test.tsx`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://example.invalid bun run build`\n- Local browser proof: LaunchDarkly Test env flag off/on/off showed Souls links hidden, then visible in nav/home/footer, then hidden again.\n\n## Notes\n\nLaunchDarkly Test env flag `clawhub-souls` was restored to off after local testing.\n",
